th zero gradient<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21231","referenceCode":"21M.3.AHL.TZ2.1g.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"a point of inflexion with zero gradient for odd values of n, where n>1 and a∈ℝ+.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"g.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.2—Increasing and decreasing functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}